The paper presents a Bayesian latent variable model for learning an efficient latent representation of high-dimensional data, with applications in image modelling and human pose prediction. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of Bayesian techniques and latent space priors, which could also make it relevant to cs.SD (Systems and Control) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
